latestIgtvVideos.title: Fellowship experience ft. Zartaj Ahmed
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
#FellowsTalk
“It was heartening to see other entrepreneurs, founders, and learn from their journeys and experiences! It was an amazing learning journey. I am very thankful to Rajeev Circle Fellowship for offering me this journey,” commends Zartaj Ahmed, Co-founder & CEO, QriosityNet.com, & Rajeev Circle Fellow ‘19. 

She further adds exciting details on how Asha enabled her first venture into better understanding the entrepreneurial space through her visit to Silicon Valley and other engaging events like Maker Faire, TiEcon, among others. 

Through our 2021 Rajeev Circle Fellowship, we seek to provide similar spaces and platforms for emerging innovators to leverage their leadership experiences.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Fellowship Experience ft. Anubha Maneshwar
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
#FellowsTalk
“In 2019, I became a Rajeev Circle fellow, and since then, my life has completely changed! Especially, getting to interact with Asha Ma’am on a day-to-day basis is a really great feeling.” excitedly elucidates Anubha Maneshwar, Founder, GirlScript Technologies and GirlScript Foundation & Rajeev Circle Fellow 2019. 
.
Anubha throws light on her entrepreneurial journey that dawned with Motwani Jadeja Foundation MakerFest in 2017 and how it aided her in excellent networking.
.
We trust that the Rajeev Circle Fellowship 2021 will present the upcoming batch with a similar experience of a lifetime.

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
#FellowsTalk
‘’I realized the real zeal inside me and that something is special about me. Rajeev Circle Fellowship has played a big role in helping me understand this,” rejoices Raziya Shaikh, Food Consultant & Founder, Bastar Food Firm and 2019 Rajeev Circle Fellow. Catch her recalling her journey from a small village of Bastar to the US and how Asha identified her talent, becoming her beacon of inspiration.

The brainchild of Raziya, Bastar Food Firm is a revolutionary step toward characterising tribal food and empowering girls and women from indigenous communities through food technology and employment opportunities.

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
“What if somebody places you in a house with the same kind of people - with similar mindsets,” recalls Shikha Shah, Founder, AtlMat & Rajeev Circle Fellow, 2019, zeroing in on her fellowship journey. latestPosts.caption:
✨Announcing our next partner at ICH 2025✨

The Motwani Jadeja Family Foundation, founded by Asha Jadeja, is dedicated to empowering young entrepreneurs in India and beyond through fellowships, direct investments, and strategic partnerships.

The foundation brings together some of the brightest young minds to challenge conventional thinking and drive innovation, impact, and action. With a strong commitment to execution, the organization works tirelessly to build capabilities that foster social change in India and beyond.

Motwani Jadeja Family Foundation supports youth in their efforts to innovate and create impact through fellowships, dynamic partnerships, and direct investments.

The foundation invests in youth and innovation as key drivers of change. It believes that supporting entrepreneurs and fostering innovation can accelerate social progress for all.

With an audacious, creative, and ambitious vision, the foundation takes risks and backs unique, bold, and untested ideas. It values experimentation, rapid prototyping, open innovation, and the power of big dreams.

The foundation partners with organizations that share its values, mission, and commitment to change. By trusting, collaborating with, and investing in its partners, the foundation enables them to take the lead in driving meaningful impact.

latestPosts.caption:
The United States and India stand together at a pivotal moment, shaping a global future through collaboration and innovation. At the Motwani Jadeja Foundation, we remain committed to fostering partnerships, empowering leaders, and connecting India with the world.

#USIndiaPartnership #GlobalIndia #MotwaniJadejaFoundation #Davos2025 #IndiaAtDavos @ashajadejamotwani

At #Davos2025, the session 'Exploring Common Ground: What the Coupling of India and America Means for Business' organized by Economist Impact and sponsored by the Motwani Jadeja Foundation, facilitated discussions on the evolving dynamics of US-India relations.

Moderated by Patrick Foulis of The Economist, the panel included Lakshmanan Chidambaram, Nadir Godrej, Asha Jadeja, Eric Garcetti, and Walter Mead. The session focused on India’s growing role in the global economy, its potential as an alternative in global supply chains, and the critical opportunities and challenges shaping the partnership between the two nations.

Motwani Jadeja Foundation remains dedicated to supporting dialogues that address global issues and foster meaningful collaboration. @ashajadejamotwani @economistimpact @theeconomistevents_
